problem: If $g(x) = 3x + 7$ and $f(x) = 5x - 9$, what is the value of $f(g(8))$?
model_solution:
Step 1: Evaluate the inner function, $g(8)$, by substituting $x = 8$ into the equation for $g(x) = 3x + 7$. 
$g(8) = 3(8) + 7$
Step 2: 
$g(8) = 3(8) + 7 = 24 + 7 = 31$
Substitute $g(8)$ into the equation for $f(x) = 5x - 9$ to find $f(g(8))$.
$f(g(8)) = 5(31) - 9$
$f(g(8)) = 5(31) - 9 = 155 - 9$
$155 - 9 = 146$
$f(g(8)) = 5(31) - 9 = 155 - 9 = 146$
$f(g(8)) = 5(31) - 9 = 155 - 9 = 146$
